### Implementation Details

The implementation follows the exact pattern recommended in the official Vercel documentation for React applications:
- The `<Analytics />` component is imported from `@vercel/analytics/react`
- It's placed inside the `<StrictMode>` wrapper alongside the main App component
- This ensures analytics tracking is active across all pages and routes

### Next Steps for Production Use

To enable analytics in your Vercel dashboard:
1. Navigate to your project in the Vercel dashboard
2. Go to the Analytics tab in the sidebar
3. Click the "Enable" button to activate Web Analytics
4. Deploy the application to Vercel
5. After deployment, analytics data will begin appearing in the dashboard

